42#define RSN_SELECTOR(a, b, c, d) \
43 ((((u32) (a)) << 24) | (((u32) (b)) << 16) | (((u32) (c)) << 8) | \
44 (u32) (d))

142#define WPA_CAPABILITY_PREAUTH BIT(0)

164/* IEEE 802.11, 8.5.2 EAPOL-Key frames */
165#define WPA_KEY_INFO_TYPE_MASK ((u16) (BIT(0) | BIT(1) | BIT(2)))
166#define WPA_KEY_INFO_TYPE_AKM_DEFINED 0
167#define WPA_KEY_INFO_TYPE_HMAC_MD5_RC4 BIT(0)
168#define WPA_KEY_INFO_TYPE_HMAC_SHA1_AES BIT(1)
169#define WPA_KEY_INFO_TYPE_AES_128_CMAC 3
170#define WPA_KEY_INFO_KEY_TYPE BIT(3) /* 1 = Pairwise, 0 = Group key */
171/* bit4..5 is used in WPA, but is reserved in IEEE 802.11i/RSN */
172#define WPA_KEY_INFO_KEY_INDEX_MASK (BIT(4) | BIT(5))
173#define WPA_KEY_INFO_KEY_INDEX_SHIFT 4
174#define WPA_KEY_INFO_INSTALL BIT(6) /* pairwise */
175#define WPA_KEY_INFO_TXRX BIT(6) /* group */
176#define WPA_KEY_INFO_ACK BIT(7)
177#define WPA_KEY_INFO_MIC BIT(8)
178#define WPA_KEY_INFO_SECURE BIT(9)
179#define WPA_KEY_INFO_ERROR BIT(10)
180#define WPA_KEY_INFO_REQUEST BIT(11)
181#define WPA_KEY_INFO_ENCR_KEY_DATA BIT(12) /* IEEE 802.11i/RSN only */
182#define WPA_KEY_INFO_SMK_MESSAGE BIT(13)

185struct wpa_eapol_key {
186 u8 type;
187 /* Note: key_info, key_length, and key_data_length are unaligned */
188 u8 key_info[2]; /* big endian */
189 u8 key_length[2]; /* big endian */
190 u8 replay_counter[WPA_REPLAY_COUNTER_LEN];
191 u8 key_nonce[WPA_NONCE_LEN];
192 u8 key_iv[16];
193 u8 key_rsc[WPA_KEY_RSC_LEN];
194 u8 key_id[8]; /* Reserved in IEEE 802.11i/RSN */
195 /* variable length Key MIC field */
196 /* big endian 2-octet Key Data Length field */
197 /* followed by Key Data Length bytes of Key Data */
198} STRUCT_PACKED;

207/**
208 * struct wpa_ptk - WPA Pairwise Transient Key
209 * IEEE Std 802.11i-2004 - 8.5.1.2 Pairwise key hierarchy
210 */
211struct wpa_ptk {
212 u8 kck[WPA_KCK_MAX_LEN]; /* EAPOL-Key Key Confirmation Key (KCK) */
213 u8 kek[WPA_KEK_MAX_LEN]; /* EAPOL-Key Key Encryption Key (KEK) */
214 u8 tk[WPA_TK_MAX_LEN]; /* Temporal Key (TK) */
215 u8 kck2[WPA_KCK_MAX_LEN]; /* FT reasoc Key Confirmation Key (KCK2) */
216 u8 kek2[WPA_KEK_MAX_LEN]; /* FT reassoc Key Encryption Key (KEK2) */
217 size_t kck_len;
218 size_t kek_len;
219 size_t tk_len;
220 size_t kck2_len;
221 size_t kek2_len;
222 int installed; /* 1 if key has already been installed to driver */
223};

237/* WPA IE version 1
238 * 00-50-f2:1 (OUI:OUI type)
239 * 0x01 0x00 (version; little endian)
240 * (all following fields are optional:)
241 * Group Suite Selector (4 octets) (default: TKIP)
242 * Pairwise Suite Count (2 octets, little endian) (default: 1)
243 * Pairwise Suite List (4 * n octets) (default: TKIP)
244 * Authenticated Key Management Suite Count (2 octets, little endian)
245 * (default: 1)
246 * Authenticated Key Management Suite List (4 * n octets)
247 * (default: unspec 802.1X)
248 * WPA Capabilities (2 octets, little endian) (default: 0)
249 */
250
251struct wpa_ie_hdr {
252 u8 elem_id;
253 u8 len;
254 u8 oui[4]; /* 24-bit OUI followed by 8-bit OUI type */
255 u8 version[2]; /* little endian */
256} STRUCT_PACKED;
257
258
259/* 1/4: PMKID
260 * 2/4: RSN IE
261 * 3/4: one or two RSN IEs + GTK IE (encrypted)
262 * 4/4: empty
263 * 1/2: GTK IE (encrypted)
264 * 2/2: empty
265 */
266
267/* RSN IE version 1
268 * 0x01 0x00 (version; little endian)
269 * (all following fields are optional:)
270 * Group Suite Selector (4 octets) (default: CCMP)
271 * Pairwise Suite Count (2 octets, little endian) (default: 1)
272 * Pairwise Suite List (4 * n octets) (default: CCMP)
273 * Authenticated Key Management Suite Count (2 octets, little endian)
274 * (default: 1)
275 * Authenticated Key Management Suite List (4 * n octets)
276 * (default: unspec 802.1X)
277 * RSN Capabilities (2 octets, little endian) (default: 0)
278 * PMKID Count (2 octets) (default: 0)
279 * PMKID List (16 * n octets)
280 * Management Group Cipher Suite (4 octets) (default: AES-128-CMAC)
281 */
282
283struct rsn_ie_hdr {
284 u8 elem_id; /* WLAN_EID_RSN */
285 u8 len;
286 u8 version[2]; /* little endian */
287} STRUCT_PACKED;
